AWS Transit Gateway (TGW) is a powerful networking service that acts like a central hub to connect multiple VPCs, on-premises networks (via VPN or Direct Connect), and even other AWS accounts. Think of it as a “cloud router” that simplifies complex multi-VPC architectures.

🔑 Core Features
Hub-and-Spoke Model → Instead of creating dozens of peering connections, you connect each VPC to the TGW.

Scalable → Supports thousands of VPCs and connections.

Centralized Routing → Route tables are managed at the TGW level.

Cross-Region Support → Can connect VPCs across AWS regions.

Integration → Works with VPN, Direct Connect, and AWS PrivateLink.

📊 Transit Gateway vs VPC Peering
Feature	          VPC Peering	                                        Transit Gateway
Topology	    Point-to-point	                                        Hub-and-spoke
Scale	       Limited (no transitive routing)	                      Thousands of VPCs
Routing       	Manual per VPC	                                      Centralized at TGW
Cross-Region	Supported	                                             Supported
Cost	       Cheaper for few VPCs	                                More cost-effective at scale
Use Case	   Simple 1-to-1 VPC links	                            Complex multi-VPC, hybrid cloud


⚙️ How It Works (Step-by-Step)
Create Transit Gateway in AWS console.

Attach VPCs → Each VPC connects to TGW via a TGW attachment.

Configure TGW Route Tables → Decide how traffic flows between VPCs.

Update VPC Route Tables → Point traffic for other VPCs to the TGW attachment.

Enable Cross-Region Peering if needed.

Test Connectivity → Instances in different VPCs communicate via private IPs.

🚫 Limitations
Higher cost compared to simple peering.

Requires careful route table design to avoid blackholes.

No automatic DNS resolution across VPCs (must configure).

🧠 Best Practices
Use TGW for large-scale, multi-VPC architectures.

Keep route tables organized (segment workloads by environment).

Combine with AWS Resource Access Manager (RAM) to share TGW across accounts.

Monitor traffic with Transit Gateway Flow Logs.

✅ Bottom Line: Transit Gateway is the enterprise-grade solution for connecting multiple VPCs and hybrid networks, offering centralized control and scalability that VPC peering alone cannot handle.